Persian Gulf Stocks: Drake & Scull and Saudi Arabia’s Amiantit

-- B y   Z a h r a   H a n k i r
-- 
2011-09-28T09:11:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-28/persian-gulf-stocks-drake-scull-and-saudi-arabia-s-amiantit.html
The  DFM General Index (DFMGI)  lost 0.5
percent to 1,441.42 at 12:32 p.m. in Dubai.  Saudi Arabia ’s
 Tadawul All Share Index (SASEIDX)  slipped 0.1 percent and the Kuwait Stock
Exchange Unweighted Index declined 0.2 percent.  The following shares were active in the Persian Gulf
region. Stock symbols are in parentheses.  Drake & Scull International (DSI)  PJSC fell for a second
day, decreasing 0.7 percent to 82.2 fils. The Dubai-based
construction company had its price estimate cut 9 percent to 100
fils, or 1 dirham, at Morgan Stanley.  Saudi Arabian Amiantit Co. (SAAC)   gained for a second
day this week, advancing 1 percent to 15.1 riyals. The building
materials manufacturer said its Qatar unit bought a stake in a
pipes producer for 7.5 million Qatari riyals ($2.1 million).  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zahra Hankir in Dubai at 
 zhankir@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
